%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20wealthy%20parent.%20I%20believe%20if%20you%20can%20pay%20for%20your%20child's%20college%2C%20you%20should.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20offers%20and%20details%20on%20this%20page%20may%20have%20updated%20or%20changed%20since%20the%20time%20of%20publication.%20See%20our%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealthy-parent-planning-paying-kids-go-to-college-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20current%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAffiliate%20links%20for%20the%20products%20on%20this%20page%20are%20from%20partners%20that%20compensate%20us%20(see%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Four-partners%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvertiser%20disclosure%20with%20our%20list%20of%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20details).%20However%2C%20our%20opinions%20are%20our%20own.%20See%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Fhow-we-rate-student-loans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20student%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20write%20unbiased%20product%20reviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22credit%20cards%20Holly%20Johnson%20Chenonceau%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6813e09bc6ad288d147fc82a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20Holly%20Johnson.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Holly%20Johnson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%20don't%20want%20to%20saddle%20my%20kids%20with%20decades%20of%20college%20debt%2C%20so%20I'm%20saving%20money%20in%20a%20529%20savings%20plan.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20may%20have%20been%20feasible%20to%20work%20to%20attend%20college%20in%20the%20past%2C%20but%20that's%20no%20longer%20the%20case.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI'll%20also%20be%20encouraging%20them%20to%20get%20degrees%20that%20apply%20to%20the%20workforce%20and%20support%20their%20financial%20futures.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20pay%20any%20attention%20to%20the%20news%20these%20days%2C%20you%20already%20know%20that%20our%20higher%20education%20system%20is%20an%20absolute%20mess.%20The%20costs%20of%20college%20tuition%20and%20fees%20(plus%20room%20and%20board)%20keep%20increasing%20every%20year%2C%20and%20student%20borrowers%20carried%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Faverage-student-loan-debt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%20of%20%2429%2C300%20in%20student%20loan%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20last%20count.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFamilies%20with%20high%20incomes%20also%20tend%20to%20produce%20students%20with%20even%20more%20debt.%20In%20fact%2C%20students%20from%20families%20in%20the%2090th%20percentile%20for%20household%20income%20or%20higher%20carried%20average%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Fbest-private-student-loans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudent%20loan%3C%2Fa%3E%20debt%20of%20%2480%2C690%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Feconres%2Fscf%2Fdataviz%2Fscf%2Ftable%2F%23series%3AEducation_Installment_Loans%3Bdemographic%3Ainccat%3Bpopulation%3Aall%3Bunits%3Amean%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20the%20Fed%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20while%2C%20a%20scary%20percentage%20of%20college%20degrees%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffreopp.org%2Fwhitepapers%2Fdoes-college-pay-off-a-comprehensive-return-on-investment-analysis%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabsolutely%20no%20return%20on%20investment%20at%20all%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20sometimes%20even%20a%20negative%20ROI.%20Meanwhile%2C%20most%20parents%20with%20kids%20approaching%20college%20have%20no%20idea%20what%20the%20actual%20cost%20of%20a%20degree%20will%20be%20or%20how%20much%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Fneed-based-financial-aid%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20aid%3C%2Fa%3E%20they'll%20be%20eligible%20to%20receive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20would%20think%20that%20all%20of%20this%20would%20scare%20high-earning%20parents%20into%20socking%20money%20away%2C%20especially%20since%20many%20forms%20of%20financial%20aid%20for%20college%20are%20for%20students%20who%20can%20demonstrate%20financial%20need.%20However%2C%20I%20have%20found%20that%20most%20of%20my%20peers%20(including%20high%20earners)%20with%20teenage%20kids%20aren't%20in%20a%20hurry%20to%20worry%20about%20college%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20plenty%20of%20parents%20don't%20think%20it's%20their%20responsibility%20to%20pay%20for%20college%20regardless%20of%20their%20income%2C%20I%20personally%20believe%20those%20with%20the%20means%20should%20%3Cem%3Eat%20least%20try%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20save%20money%20for%20college%2C%20trade%20school%2C%20or%20any%20other%20career%20training%20path%20their%20child%20might%20take.%20Here's%20why%20I%20save%20for%20my%20kid's%20college%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-529-plans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E529%20savings%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20plan%20to%20cover%20funding%20shortfalls%20myself%20(at%20least%20through%20the%20undergraduate%20level)%20when%20the%20time%20comes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2238af981d-4ee3-4d8d-a361-e19b9a5e08d2%5C%22%3EA%20parent's%20high%20income%20can%20limit%20financial%20aid%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20parent%20of%20two%20girls%2C%20ages%2014%20and%2016%2C%20I%20saw%20the%20writing%20on%20the%20wall%20when%20it%20came%20to%20funding%20college%20very%20early%20on.%20The%20information%20shared%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Fhow-to-fill-out-the-fafsa-financial-aid%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFAFSA%3C%2Fa%3E%20helps%20schools%20and%20government%20agencies%20assess%20%3Cem%3Emy%20own%20financial%20situation%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20so%20earning%20a%20lot%20and%20having%20more%20assets%20will%20not%20help%20my%20kids%20qualify%20for%20considerable%20(or%20any)%20financial%20aid%20for%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20our%20household%20income%20and%20assets%20are%20going%20to%20hold%20my%20kids%20back%20from%20receiving%20many%20types%20of%20financial%20aid%20for%20college%2C%20then%20it%20seems%20crazy%20to%20act%20like%20I%20am%20off%20the%20hook%20for%20all%20college%20costs.%20I'm%20not%20saying%20all%20high-earning%20parents%20should%20agree%20to%20pay%20for%20college%20in%20its%20entirety%2C%20but%20I%20am%20saying%20that%20most%20of%20us%20could%20save%20%3Cem%3Esomething%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3Efor%20school%20during%20the%2018-year%20period%20before%20our%20kids%20leave%20the%20nest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2234990119-20e6-46ca-9167-cc14568d7695%5C%22%3EI%20don't%20want%20my%20kids%20to%20begin%20their%20adult%20lives%20with%20debt%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20student%20loan%20debt%20most%20borrowers%20carry%20scares%20me%2C%20especially%20since%20many%20repayment%20plans%20for%20federal%20and%20private%20student%20loans%20last%20for%20up%20to%2020%20or%2025%20years.%20Setting%20them%20up%20to%20make%20student%20loan%20payments%20until%20they're%20well%20into%20their%2040s%3F%20No%2C%20thank%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20I%20don't%20know%20about%20you%2C%20but%20I%20absolutely%20hate%20the%20idea%20of%20my%20kids%20beginning%20their%20adult%20lives%20with%20a%20considerable%20debt%20burden.%20After%20all%2C%20this%20is%20a%20time%20when%20they%20might%20want%20to%20start%20a%20family%20or%20begin%20saving%20up%20to%20purchase%20a%20home%20of%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225303d0e3-5310-4253-a638-20dc30f8ea29%5C%22%3EIt's%20no%20longer%20feasible%20to%20'pay%20as%20you%20go'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20case%20you're%20wondering%2C%20I've%20heard%20the%20argument%20that%20some%20parents%20worked%20and%20paid%20for%20college%20as%20they%20went.%20If%20they%20did%20it%20back%20in%20the%2080s%20or%2090s%2C%20their%20kids%20can%20do%20it%2C%20too%2C%20right%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20college%20is%20way%20more%20expensive%20than%20it%20used%20to%20be%2C%20and%20this%20is%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20is%20rising%20rapidly.%20According%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fresearch.collegeboard.org%2Ftrends%2Fcollege-pricing%2Fhighlights%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECollegeBoard%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Faverage-college-tuition%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%20college%20cost%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20attend%20a%20public%20four-year%2C%20in-state%20school%20was%20%2411%2C610%20for%20the%202024-2025%20academic%20year.%20That's%20just%20for%20one%20year%20of%20school%2C%20and%20it%20doesn't%20include%20the%20average%20annual%20cost%20for%20room%20and%20board%20(%2413%2C310).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20the%20average%20cost%20for%20a%20four-year%20degree%20from%20a%20public%20college%20is%20currently%20around%20six%20figures%2C%20give%20or%20take.%20While%20it's%20possible%20for%20students%20to%20work%20during%20school%2C%20most%20can't%20juggle%20earning%20that%20much%20and%20excelling%20in%20their%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226d69ce12-a1c7-43e7-ab7b-637dff7fb6b0%5C%22%3ECollege%20is%20%3Cem%3Eusually%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20good%20investment%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20college%20degrees%20don't%20provide%20a%20good%20ROI%20(or%20any%20ROI)%2C%20studies%20show%20that%20college%20is%20still%20a%20good%20investment%20overall.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Femp%2Fchart-unemployment-earnings-education.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EData%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20average%20weekly%20earnings%20for%20someone%20with%20no%20college%20degree%20came%20in%20at%20%24930%20in%202024%2C%20compared%20to%20%241%2C543%20for%20those%20with%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20and%20%241%2C840%20for%20graduates%20with%20a%20master's%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20I%20plan%20to%20urge%20my%20kids%20to%20attend%20one%20of%20our%20excellent%20state%20schools%20for%20more%20affordable%20tuition%20and%20to%20help%20them%20find%20a%20degree%20program%20that%20applies%20to%20the%20actual%20workforce%20and%20provides%20a%20solid%20foundation%20for%20their%20financial%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20no%20%26quot%3Bfeel-good%26quot%3B%20degree%20programs%20that%20don't%20apply%20to%20real-world%20jobs%20or%20industries%2C%20at%20least%20if%20I'm%20paying.%20We%20have%20already%20started%20that%20conversation%20in%20our%20household%2C%20so%20this%20won't%20take%20my%20kids%20by%20surprise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20high-earning%20parent%2C%20I%20cannot%20think%20of%20a%20better%20investment%20I%20could%20make%20than%20paying%20for%20my%20children's%20undergraduate%20education.%20And%20with%20the%20way%20the%20world%20is%20going%2C%20they're%20going%20to%20need%20all%20the%20help%20they%20can%20get.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealthy-parent-planning-paying-kids-go-to-college-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1746274921000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5cb4cbb2895511023269ef4b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealthy-parent-planning-paying-kids-go-to-college-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Student%20loan%20debt%20often%20takes%20decades%20to%20pay%20off.%20I%20don't%20want%20my%20kids%20to%20start%20their%20adult%20lives%20already%20in%20debt%2C%20so%20I'm%20paying%20the%20bill.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22holly%40clubthrifty.c