king%20on%20eggshells%26quot%3B%20policy%2C%20would%20ensure%20faster%20and%20more%20impartial%20investigations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToo%20often%20at%20the%20Defense%20Department%2C%20there%20are%20complaints%20made%20for%20certain%20reasons%20that%20can't%20be%20verified%20that%20have%20ended%20people's%20careers%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FSecDef%2Fstatus%2F1915785070599626788%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%257Ctwcamp%255Etweetembed%257Ctwterm%255E1915785070599626788%257Ctwgr%255Ec2e1aedda71fa96447e1c997b62df03c16dace87%257Ctwcon%255Es1_%26ref_url%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fmustreadalaska.com%252Fhegseth-signs-order-no-more-walking-on-eggshells-policy-to-end-weaponization-of-complaints%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20accompanying%20video%2C%20calling%20some%20complaints%20%26quot%3Bnonsense.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20current%20and%20former%20female%20service%20members%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20they%20worry%20potential%20changes%20could%20reverse%20recent%20progress%20in%20addressing%20problems%20like%20hazing%2C%20sexual%20harassment%2C%20racism%2C%20and%20social%20media%20misconduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetired%20Marine%20Corps%20Lt.%20Col.%20Kate%20Germano%2C%20author%20of%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BFight%20Like%20a%20Girl%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI%20that%20%26quot%3Bit%20seems%20that%20those%20who%20are%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20pecking%20order%20will%20be%20the%20most%20adversely%20impacted%20by%20the%20%5Blatest%5D%20change%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20women%20and%20people%20of%20color.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Marine%20officer%20who%20has%20led%20investigations%20told%20BI%20the%20new%20memo%20seems%20%26quot%3Bpart%20and%20parcel%20with%20their%20effort%20to%20weaken%20participation%20of%20underrepresented%20groups.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20seem%20like%20a%20bad%20thing%20to%20prevent%20spurious%20complaints%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20speaking%20anonymously%20to%20avoid%20retaliation.%20She%20previously%20investigated%20questionable%20claims%20but%20said%20that%20she%20hates%20%26quot%3Bthe%20idea%20that%20you%20could%20be%20punished%20if%20your%20command%20doesn't%20agree%20with%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f76d43fd-1043-4a51-8868-5d8d4225e3ba%5C%22%3E'Gutting%20the%20program'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.defense.gov%2F2025%2FApr%2F25%2F2003697394%2F-1%2F-1%2F1%2FRESTORING-GOOD-ORDER-AND-DISCIPLINE-THROUGH-BALANCED-ACCOUNTABILITY.PDF%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%C2%A0memo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0titled%20%26quot%3BRestoring%20Good%20Order%20and%20Discipline%20Through%20Balanced%20Accountability%2C%26quot%3B%20orders%20the%20dismissal%20of%20complaints%20not%20substantiated%20by%20%26quot%3Bactionable%2C%20credible%20evidence.%26quot%3B%20Such%20a%20change%20could%20discredit%20anonymous%20complaints%20or%20harassment%20that%20occurs%20in%20private%2C%20said%20Rachel%20VanLandingham%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20Southwestern%20Law%20School%20and%20former%20Air%20Force%20JAG.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pentagon.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679e6af67bb3f854015b6ef3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Pentagon.%3Cp%3EJen%20Golbeck%2FSOPA%20Images%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EChanges%20to%20Department%20of%20Defense%20policies%20could%20also%20have%20an%20outsized%20impact%20on%20the%20lowest%20enlisted%20ranks%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdacowits.defense.gov%2FPortals%2F48%2FDocuments%2FReports%2F2022%2FDocuments%2FUSA%2520RFI%252017%2520(2).pdf%3Fver%3DWSsh-Ja6TmBO85pdTtAutA%253D%253D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20up%20a%20large%20share%20of%20historical%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20bias%20and%20sex-based%20discrimination%20complaints.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMilitary%20EO%20programs%20are%20responsible%20for%20ensuring%20personnel%20are%20allowed%20%26quot%3Bfull%20and%20fair%20opportunity%20for%20employment%2C%20career%20advancement%20and%20access%20to%20programs%20without%20regard%20to%20race%2C%20color%2C%20religion%2C%20national%20origin%2C%20disability%2C%20gender%2C%20age%2C%20sexual%20orientation%2C%20genetic%20information%20or%20parental%20status.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20programs%20allow%20personnel%20to%20report%20discrimination%20and%20harassment%2C%20and%20that's%20a%20good%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20Hegseth%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defense.gov%2FNews%2FNews-Stories%2FArticle%2FArticle%2F4165627%2Fhegseth-directs-review-of-equal-opportunity-complaint-process%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDoD%20news%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BBut%20what's%20not%20good%20is%20when%20these%20programs%20are%20weaponized.%20Some%20individuals%20use%20these%20programs%20in%20bad%20faith%20to%20retaliate%20against%20superiors%20or%20peers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHegseth%20did%20not%20provide%20data%20on%20the%20scope%20of%20false%20allegations%20made%20through%20the%20military's%20EO%20process%2C%20only%20saying%20in%20a%20video%20on%20X%20that%20he%20hears%20it%20%26quot%3Ball%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20secretary%20has%20personally%20faced%20what%20he%20has%20said%20were%20false%20allegations%20of%20sexual%20assault.%20In%202020%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F11%2F20%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fpolice-report-sexual-assault-claim-hegseth.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHegseth%20settled%20a%20dispute%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20woman%20who%20said%20the%20former%20TV%20host%20sexually%20assaulted%20her.%20No%20charges%20were%20ever%20filed.%20During%20his%20confirmation%20hearing%2C%20he%20said%20that%20the%20situation%20was%20%26quot%3Bfully%20investigated%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bcompletely%20cleared.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223927%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pete%20Hegseth%20speaking%20to%20the%20press.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c508b0b8b41a9673f97027%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222616%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDefense%20Secretary%20Pete%20Hegseth%20has%20been%20at%20the%20center%20of%20numerous%20shake-ups%20at%20the%20Pentagon%20in%20recent%20months.%3Cp%3EOmar%20Marques%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEO%20programs%20have%20been%20scrutinized%20before.%20Some%20critics%20have%20said%20the%20policies%20make%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airforcetimes.com%2Fopinion%2Fcommentary%2F2019%2F09%2F06%2Fthe-tools-of-character-assassination%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bcharacter%20assassination%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20easy%20for%20disgruntled%20personnel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20things%20that%20could%20be%20worked%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20VanLandingham%20said.%20But%20with%20this%20memo%2C%20she%20said%2C%20it%20seems%20like%20%26quot%3Bthey're%20just%20gutting%20the%20program.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202020%20investigation%20by%20Reuters%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Finvestigates%2Fspecial-report%2Fusa-military-civilrights%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20troops%20file%20complaints%20at%20much%20lower%20rates%20than%20DoD%20civilians%2C%20suggesting%20a%20fear%20of%20retaliation%20among%20active%20duty%20personnel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVanLandingham%20said%20that%20making%20a%20false%20allegation%20is%20an%20offense%20that's%20already%20covered%20by%20the%20Uniformed%20Code%20of%20Military%20Justice%2C%20which%20criminalizes%20false%20official%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChanges%20to%20the%20EO%20program%20could%20create%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20victims%20who%20might%20fear%20reporting%20harassment%2C%20she%20added%2C%20highlighting%20that%20some%20troops%20may%20avoid%20submitting%20complaints%20for%20fear%20of%20retaliation%20or%20being%20ostracized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20never%20tell%20anyone%20to%20make%20an%20EO%20complaint%2C%20especially%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20female%20veteran%20who%20previously%20submitted%20a%20complaint%20alleging%20sexual%20harassment%20and%20said%20she%20later%20faced%20retaliation.%20She%20spoke%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20because%20she%20is%20seeking%20federal%20employment.%20BI%20reviewed%20related%20documentation%20between%20her%20and%20her%20command.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20they%20don't%20like%20you%2C%20it's%20now%20definitely%20a%20way%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20you%20and%20adversely%20affect%20your%20career%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20woman%2C%20who%20is%20on%20active%20duty%2C%20told%20BI%20she%20fears%20the%20changes%20will%20discourage%20troops%20from%20filing%20complaints.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20feels%20like%20a%20slap%20in%20the%20face%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224c933fbc-02dc-4645-bc56-bfd1b9bd6297%5C%22%3EUnanswered%20questions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20guess%20the%20biggest%20question%20is%20who%20decides%20what%20is%20or%20is%20not%20credible%20information%20or%20what%20is%20fair%2C%26quot%3B%20Germano%20said.%20She%20said%20the%20military's%20process%20for%20internal%20investigations%20is%20already%20thorny%20%E2%80%94%20such%20investigations%20are%20often%20done%20by%20troops%20with%20little%20to%20no%20meaningful%20investigative%20experience%2C%20often%20bestowed%20upon%20them%20as%20a%20secondary%20duty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECasting%20greater%20doubt%20on%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20claims%20could%20make%20things%20even%20trickier%2C%20Germano%20said%2C%20explaining%20decisions%20may%20be%20influenced%20by%20the%20perspectives%20of%20the%20command's%20senior%20members%2C%20based%20on%20the