vulnerability.%20The%20repeal%20of%20the%20Beedi%20Workers%20Welfare%20Fund%20Act%2C%201976%2C%20in%202019%20led%20to%20the%20discontinuation%20of%20key%20welfare%20measures%20such%20as%20scholarships%20for%20workers%E2%80%99%20children%20and%20access%20to%20free%20healthcare%20despite%20the%20well-documented%20health%20risks%20associated%20with%20%3Cem%3Ebeedi%3C%2Fem%3E%20work%2C%20including%20skin%20ailments%20and%20the%20absence%20of%20basic%20infrastructure%20like%20toilets.%20This%20has%20left%20many%20workers%20without%20state%20benefits%20that%20once%20served%20as%20a%20crucial%20safety%20net.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mssnmp.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMahila%20Shram%20Sewa%20Nyas%20(MSSN)%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20has%20stepped%20in%20with%20a%20community-driven%20model%20rooted%20in%20policy%20advocacy%20and%20empowerment.%20Working%20across%20seven%20districts%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20MSSN%20supports%20women%20informal%20workers%20through%20livelihood%20trainings%2C%20cooperative%20credit%20societies%2C%20leadership%20development%2C%20and%20legal%20aid.%20They%20also%20work%20with%20local%20governments%20to%20restore%20and%20strengthen%20welfare%20provisions%2C%20ensuring%20that%20women%20workers%E2%80%99%20voices%20are%20represented%20in%20policy%20spaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommunity%20structures%20like%20Seva%20Samitis%20and%20Nigrani%20Samitis%20further%20deepen%20this%20impact%20by%20enabling%20collective%20action%2C%20improving%20access%20to%20essential%20services%20like%20drainage%20and%20electricity%2C%20and%20sustaining%20pressure%20for%20systemic%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2FTBI-featured-image-19_11zon-1-1746189236